sentences: In addition to his extensive solo work, Wess is remembered for his time in Count Basie's band from the early 1950s into the 1960s.
He played tenor sax with Count Basie from 1953 to 1964, doubling on flute.
From 1959 to 1964, he won the Down Beat magazine critics' poll for flute.
He was a member of Clark Terry's big band from 1967 into the 1970s and played in the New York Jazz Quartet (with Roland Hanna).
He was a member of Clark Terry's big band from 1967 into the 1970s and played in the New York Jazz Quartet (with Roland Hanna).
In 1968 he contributed to the album The Jazz Composer's Orchestra.
In the 2000s, Wess released two albums with Hank Jones.
In 2007, Wess was named an NEA Jazz Master by the U.S. National Endowment for the Arts.
Wess died from a heart attack related to kidney failure on October 30, 2013.
